HEADWORD: photocell
<hw>pho"to*cell`</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧"t⟦osl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧l`)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>An electrical device which changes voltage or resistance upon
exposure to light, used to detect and measure light and other
radiations.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> photoelectric cell, electric eye.</syn>⟦br⟧
